                to complete the hiding process. Use the back arrow or the show/hide 
                tool to bring the quadrilateral back into view.
            </p>
        </aside>
    </task>
    <task>
        <introduction>
            <p>
                An isometry affects all points in the plane, not just those pictured. 
                Draw three new points:
                point <m>H</m> lying on side <m>\overline{BC}</m>, 
                point <m>I</m> lying in the exterior of quadrilateral <m>ABCD</m>, 
                and point <m>J</m> lying in the interior of <m>ABCD</m>.   
            </p>
        </introduction>
        <task>
            <statement>
                <p>
                    Sketch point <m>H'</m>, the image of <m>H</m> under the transformation that takes
